                                                                        Q11.Business question
                                                     What behaviors are common among customers who churn?
            Query
SELECT
churned,
ROUND(AVG(sessions_per_month),2),
ROUND(AVG(support_tickets),2),
ROUND(AVG(nps_score),2)
FROM user_monthly
GROUP BY churned;

                                                                      Q12.Business question
                                            Which customer groups should be prioritized by Customer Success teams?
                  Query
SELECT
CASE WHEN company_size <=50 THEN 'small_company'
WHEN company_size BETWEEN 51 AND 300 THEN 'Medium_company'
ELSE 'large_company'
END AS company_size_group,
plan_type,
SUM(total_revenue) total_revenue,
SUM(ltv_12m)lifetime_value,
ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN churned ='Churned' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)*100.0/COUNT(*),2)Churn_rate,
COUNT(*) AS total_customers,
SUM(CASE WHEN churned='Churned' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS churned_users
FROM users
GROUP BY CASE WHEN company_size <=50 THEN 'small_company'
WHEN company_size BETWEEN 51 AND 300 THEN 'Medium_company'
ELSE 'large_company' END,plan_type
ORDER BY lifetime_value DESC;

                                                                                          Findings:
Here we are focusing on those with the highest churn rate and those that will generate the highest lifetime value
The medium sized company that subscribe to the business plan type had the highest lifetime value while the large sized company that subscribed to the enterprise plan type had the highest churn rate

                                                                                       Why did it happen?
Most of our users with low sactisfaction score tend to have the highest churn rate because these users tend to experience issues while using the product

                                                                                      
                                                                                  Why should leadership care?
Losing these set users with the highest churn rate will affect our revenue and also acquisition of new users or customers will require more revenue to used for the new users
